    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hirsch</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 20,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 90.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Dispatch No. 123 of the 3d instant from your
                        legation is received. Your note of the 1st instant to the minister of state,
                        in the case of the assault on Messrs. Knapp and Raynolds by Moussa Bey in
                        1883, is regarded as a most excellent presentation of the matter as it
                        stands at this juncture.</p>
                <p>Awaiting the reply of the Porte,</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
